        <name>10.1.2.1 Addition and subtraction of complex numbers</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;h3&gt;Addition and subtraction of complex numbers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(z\)&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(w\)&lt;/span&gt; be any two complex numbers &lt;span class="math inline"&gt; where \(z=a+i b\) and \(w=c+i d\)&lt;/span&gt; then 
&lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\[z+w=(a+c)+i(b+d),\] \[z-w=(a-c)+i(b-d).\]&lt;/span&gt; For example if &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(z=2-3i\)&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;\(w=-4+2i\)&lt;/span&gt; then &lt;span class="math inline"&gt;
\[z+w=\{2+(-4)\}+\{(-3)+2\}i =-2-i,\]
\[z-w=\{2-(-4)\}+\{(-3)-2\}i =6-5i\]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
